{meta: title We Danced On The Oregon Trail}
{meta: artist Red Steagall}
{meta: composer Red Steagall and Richard O'Brien}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]We crossed the Plat River the [F]wagons were [C]full
Of [F]women [G7]children and [C]men
We turned toward the west and the [F]new life out [C]there
We'll not see [G7]Nebraska [C]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Then the [Dm]days turned to [G7]weeks and the [Am]mud and the rain
The [Dm]oxen were tired of the [E7]grind
[Dm]Stories of Indians [Am]death and disease
[E7]Constantly worked on my [Am]mind [G7]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Then a [C]baby was born to the [F]unsensitive [C]girl
I [G7]smiled when I heard his first [Am]wail 
Then as [F]Ben played his [G7]fiddle and [C]Will played his [D7]harp
We [C]danced on the [G7]Oregon [C]trail
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
The weather was kind as we [F]moved across the [C]plains
Then [F]fever struck [G7]our little [C]band
We buried the young Simpson [F]girl and her [C]child
On a bluff where Fort [G7]Laramie [C]stands
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Fort [Dm]Hall on the [G7]Snake was a [Am]wonderful sight
We [Dm]cheered as we hurried on [E7]in
The [Dm]Cheyenne had trailed us the [Am]last several days
We were [E7]glad to find shelter and [Am]friends[G7]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
They [C]made us feel welcome we [F]needed the [C]rest
We [G7]feasted on Elk meat and [Am]Quail
Then as [F]Ben played his [G7]fiddle and [C]Will played his [D7]harp
We [C]danced on the [G7]Oregon [C]trail
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Then the Black Feet attacked us we [F]lost several [C]men
My [F]Pa was the [G7]first one to [C]fall
I left him out there by the [F]side of the [C]trail
Where the sage ends and the [G7]Coyotes [C]call
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
We [Dm]reached Fort Van[G7]couver the [Am]seventh of May
We [Dm]traveled for most of the [E7]year
But [Dm]Columbia Valley [Am]became our new home
If [E7]only my poppa was [Am]here[G7]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
I [C]married young Kathy back [F]late in the [C]fall
They [G7]toasted with fine Irish [Am]Ale [C]
Then as [F]Ben played his [G7]fiddle and [C]Will played his [D7]harp
We [C]danced on the [G7]Oregon [Am]Trail
We [C]danced at the [G7]end of the [C]trail
{end_of_verse}
